Key Match Events: Dominik Szoboszlai scored the first goal for Hungary in the 38th minute.
Szoboszlai converted a penalty in the second half to make it 2-0 for Hungary.
Hungarian goalkeeper Dénes Dibusz made key saves against Edin Džeko.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Hungary's victory over Bosnia and Herzegovina puts them tied on points with the Netherlands in their group.
Hungary's last game in the group stage will be against Germany at the Puskás Arena in Budapest.
Hungary aims to make amends with fans after a heavy 5-0 loss to Germany in the away leg.
